sentence_text: It's a reality that girls go through 'that time of the month.' Hygiene products are a basic need.
It is a reality of existence.
Some families provide them for adolescents.
Some families don't for a variety of reasons.
Sometimes families are too poor and can't afford to buy feminine hygiene products.
Some families are neglectful and simply don't make it a priority to provide these products.
It would be a shame for a student to be in school and not have a pad or tampon when it is needed.
Therefore, schools need to be ready.
Every school should have a plan.
Just like they have a plan if a student falls and needs ice for her knee, or a band-aid or if there's an emergency, there should be a plan if someone needs a feminine hygiene product.
Schools should make sure that pads and tampons are easily accessible for students.
They should be comfortable and effective first and foremost.
Secondly, they should be easy to access.
No one wants to go back to the nurse and say, 'I need a pad.' There should be a designated place in every restroom.
That means it's easily accessible and available for anyone to take.
And everyone will be on their way to  a happier period!
Sooner or later people will become anti-social.
People will forget how to deal with others in person.
People will lose their patience.
We will develop problems communicating with others due to the mostly the loss of personal connection with others.
We have seen this in the development of gaming for instance.

What seems like a long time ago, if you wanted to play a multiplayer game, you had multiple controllers, food, snacks, drinks, and your friends would come over to your house to play (or you would go to theirs).
These friends were not total strangers.
Sure, there was fun loving jibbing each other sometimes, but no one felt like they were really under personal attack.
Today if you play a game online, you stay at home and connect your PC or console to the internet and join an online game.
Gamers have become toxic to each other across because there is no longer a sense of personal connectedness or friendship at all.
It's easy to call someone a loser when there is no consequences for said action.
The same thing will take place across screens for work and school as time goes by.
People will not feel that sense of comradery at work anymore.
Kids won't develop a social sense of friendship with kids outside the home anymore, and teachers won't feel as dedicated to their students or bosses to their employees.
You look up and see the bee flitting about in front of you.
You're not sure what to say, since bees stress you out so much that it's hard to think.
The bee's wings are moving quickly and nervously.
This makes you feel nervous, because you know that bees are very sensitive to their surroundings.
Aren't they like dogs?
Dogs can sense anxiety and fear and when they sense that, this is when they start biting.
So if this bee senses that you're nervous, it might sting you.
You attempt to soothe your emotions, but find it challenging.
You ask the bee why he's approached you, and he says that he's been sent by the queen to give you a message.
'What's the message?'
you ask.
The bee conveys that the queen is curious if you would be interested in joining her for a picnic.
'Why would I have a picnic with the queen?'
The bee says that he's really been sent to be your personal butler and that the invitation to picnic with the queen is a rare opportunity, not to be taken lightly.
You say you are unsure.
'After all, I'm deathly allergic to bees.'
The bee mentions that he has received special training to be gentle and assures that he will keep his stinger hidden.
And he promises that the queen doesn't want anything bad to happen to you either, so she'll be sure not to sting you too.
He also promises that the picnic food will be delicious, including all your favorite foods with a special treat at the end.
You agree.
After all, what is there to lose?
You love picnic food, and you're promised a spread that includes all your favorites, which include fried chicken, egg salad sandwiches, macaroni salad, potato salad, and chocolate cake.
So off you go with your butler bee to find the queen.
When you do, you're intrigued because she looks like a normal bee, but she's wearing a crown.
She is donning a lengthy, billowy gown and is seated on a picnic blanket laid out on a meadow covered with blossoms.
You take a seat next to her and she passes you a plate of fried chicken.
You're taken aback because you didn't realize that bees could prepare food, but this chicken is delicious.
The exterior is crunchy while the interior is moist.
You consume two pieces and then request a sandwich.
You are given an egg salad sandwich by the queen, and you proceed to consume it.
After requesting a macaroni salad, the queen presents you with a bowl of it.
After consuming it, you request a serving of potato salad.
You are handed a bowl of the dish by the queen and proceed to consume it.
You were going to request chocolate cake, but you changed your mind.
You're so full you could almost burst.
The queen laughs.
She finds you humorous.
'Why did you bring me here?'
you ask.
The queen smiles.
'I wanted to show you my kingdom,' she says.
She tells you that she noticed that you have decided to plant a garden recently in your backyard.
However, you've sprayed a bunch of insecticide everywhere, and that is very concerning to her since some of her bees in her kingdom have gotten sick or died after flitting over to your garden.
She wants you to stop using the insecticide.
'But I'm allergic to most bugs and bees, and thus I need to keep them at bay,' you tell her.
'No,' she says.
'I'm giving my personal orders to my kingdom that no bee shall sting you ever, as long as you get rid of the insecticide.'
You think about this offer and decide to take the queen up on it.
After all, you don't want to be stung, and she's pretty nice.
She's even treated you to a delicious picnic.
So you agree to stop using the insecticide.
The queen is happy with this arrangement and tells you that she'll be sure to send her butler bee to you every now and then to check up on you.
She tells you that if you ever need anything from her kingdom, you should just let your butler bee know.
You tell her that you'll do just that!
It does allow you to enjoy a book while you are doing other things.
It enables you to experience a book without experiencing the strain of reading.
You can use the time to sit in the bathtub and just listen.
That can be very relaxing.
Additionally, it provides you with extra time to listen to the story, especially while driving.
Imagine going on a cross country trip and bringing audiobooks with you.
You could easily get through multiple books even while driving.
If you had brought regular books then you might have been lucky to get through one in your downtime.
Listening to an audiobook has its drawbacks.
You don't get that connection that you otherwise would have had from holding the physical book.
Also out of sight out of mind comes into play as well.
If you don't see a physical book sitting on your coffee table then it can be easy to forget that you were even reading in the first place.
That's part of living a hectic life.
It's gotten so easy to access audiobooks that they are just as available as physical books now.
You can even download them for free via your library's app.
You no longer have to purchase an audiobook.
That is a game changer.
So which is the right choice, an audio book or a regular book?
It all comes down to your circumstances and the reason for your reading.
If you are busy and and otherwise wouldn't have time to read then an audiobook is a great choice.
If you however have more free time then you can't beat a regular book.
The most important thing though is to just keep taking in these stories that are available to us.
The way they are delivered isn't as important as just doing it.
The people who took the drug, called Ivima, start losing their minds.
They turn aggressive and suspicious.
The country has been put into a long-term lockdown because the people who took it are slowly turning into elderly mass murderers.
Just last week, a 78-year-old male slaughtered 35 people in a grocery store, claiming that they were all aliens.
There has been a public order to round up and humanely execute all people who have taken the drug for over 59 years.
There has been outrage and uproar over the massive genocide of the elderly, but slowly and surely, each person turns into a mass murderer after they have taken the drug for almost sixty years.
The government, being run mainly by old people in the past, has been overrun by youth.
They stormed the capitol building to remove the elderly congressmen and women that were trying to prevent the executions from taking place.
They euthanized everyone over the age of seventy.
The youthful population currently governs the government.
They will continue to cull the elderly that have taken Ivima since their twenties, and then the country will go into a period of darkness due to the loss suffered by nearly every family.
Never again will they take a drug like that, never again will they cull the population.
She holds onto her self-control and slowly, so as not to wake him, she gets out of bed.
She grabs her phone as she leaves the bedroom heading for the bathroom, the only place with a door that will lock.
She phones the police.
The authorities show up and she recounts her tale to them.
Right in the middle of it her boyfriend emerges from the bedroom and denies there's anyone else in there.
The police search.
They give her a gimlet stare.
They pull her boyfriend aside and suggest a visit to the ER is in order since it appears she has hallucinated.

So, he's got a choice, after the police leave he can tell her the truth, or he can take her to the ER and have them check out her mental state because the police are convinced she's a nut case and he's got to get her to the ER before she does something crazy.
What a dilemma, what should he do?
THe decides to play for time.
He'll take her to the ER, let them run a few tests, bring her home and see how things go.
He didn't find that things went so smoothly though.
The ER doc insisted she be admitted for observation.
He ordered a multitude of expensive and painful tests.
As this went on and on he figured he could never admit to her why she was really in this pickle.
She would hate him.
Their relationship would be over.
Every day she got worse.
She couldn't even sleep because of the crazies on the ward screaming all night.
She lost weight.
She looked awful.
She just wasn't the same person anymore.
He did something he never thought he would do.
He walked away, shifted his shape, and went out on the prowl for a new girlfriend.
This relationship hadn't worked out in the past and certainly wasn't now.
Too bad!
What they decide to do with their life, is primarily their decision.
Risky sports such as extreme mountain climbing, is an active decision that people take, just like other athletes that perform less risky sports.
Extreme sports are not for everyone, but for those that do choose to participate, it is their choice to do so.
They are not forced to do so, nor are the dangers hidden from them when they being investing time in the sport.

Less dangerous sports will always draw more people to it, primarily for the ease in getting proficient in said sports, but also the fact that such sports will not injure them if precautions are taken.
The same can be applied to extreme sports, as mountain climbing can be done in a risky manner, or in a way that minimizes dangers and reduces the risk for the person.

Whether a sport is then too dangerous does not change its classification, as sports are labeled not based on the risk involved in the sport, but rather how the person engages in it, and whether they compete or even cooperate with others.
Extreme sports follow the same set of guidelines as many less risky sports, but are associated with more risk.
For example, people wishing to mountain climb must learn proper techniques, invest in proper equipment, and even train on less tasking mountains before tackling more dangerous and demanding climbs.
The same is true for other extreme sports.
As for when a sport becomes unreasonable or still within reason depends primarily on the person, specifically their skill, physique, and mindset.
For example, a person who is not in good physical shape, or does not have the proper mindset to climb a mountain, will be more likely to get injured on the climb than a more experienced climber.
Thus we could say for the person that it is unreasonable for them to continue to mountain climb, until they get more experience and training.

There might as well be some level that is unobtainable for athletes and participants of an extreme sport, that might be considered based on risk and danger to be unreasonable to undertake no matter the physique and training said participants may have.
Ideally, they ought to be well informed of the risks and dangers, and well-prepared for the sport.
To disregard such considerations is to make the sport more risky than it already is, but many do make such considerations.

n the end, it is up to the person to decide what they are willing to risk in their life., and what sort of achievements they wish to accomplish, either for the notoriety or for some sense of self-worth.

Barack, you are the chosen one.
Obama gets up, says you can count on me Mr. President.

I believe it is important to strive for that level of quality.
Some might feel that they should just be left alone to mange their own business, without needing to know what is going on in the world around them.
However, nobody in modern society is an island.
A well-informed population is especially important in democratic systems.
If individuals lack information, they will not be able to make educated choices regarding their voting preferences or which legislation to endorse.
The morality and justness of a democracy hinges on the population making reasonable and informed decisions.
In this light we can see that it is selfish and dangerous to allow ourselves to be ignorant of the news.
Society only works when people are responsible not only for themselves but for each other and for the community as a whole.
We can only act to help our community when we are educated about the issues it faces.
For these reasons we must all take the responsibility to learn the news and to understand it.
In this way we can move together wisely into a better world.
The aliens are completely unaware of what awaits them.
Immediately, Matt Damon's security, which calls themselves the Ninja Rescue Team, realizes he is missing and is ready to take action.
The aliens are not ready for the Ninja Rescue Team, as they are a group of ninjas who are ready to fight to the death to get Matt Damon back to safety.
The Ninja Rescue Team first had to find where the alien is hiding.
They were aware that the alien would be concealed in a difficult-to-locate location, so they needed to come up with a strategy.
They chose to separate and look for the extraterrestrial.
Eventually one of the Ninjas found him hiding in a cave in the wilderness.
He had Mr. Damon with him in the cave.
The Ninja had to engage in a battle with the alien in order to rescue Matt Damon.
The alien was really strong so he shouted his special call to get the rest of the Ninjas there to help him.
Afterwards, all the Ninjas arrived to engage in a battle with the alien.
When the alien was almost defeated, he surrendered.
The Ninjas brought Matt Damon back to the Ninja Rescue Center to ensure his safety and well-being.
The alien thought he could hold a human hostage that day and get what he wanted from the humans, but it did not work out that way this time.
The alien learned his lesson for sure.
He discovered that messing with the Ninja Rescue Team is not a wise decision.
He will definitely not be abducting any more humans from this day forth.
This speculative sci-fi novel delves into the tale of the 'Lost Generations' as it starts.
In order to prolong their lives, the Lost Generations innovate technologies that halt the aging process.
They construct orbital habitats and underground cities that can sustain themselves and are highly automated. The research gene therapy to effectively stop the aging process.
Their drug is better and more effective than the one that was initially given to everyone under age 26.

As the Lucky Ones went on with their lives, blissfully unaware that they were ticking time bombs for horrid side effects, The Lost ones were building and evolving and making their own spaces better in the world.
They were ready when the side effects eventually occurred.
The side effects hit the Lucky Ones with the blow of a bull hitting the matador.
They were unprepared and unwilling to accept that their mortality may one day be imminent.
The side effects were so terrible that all they could think of was death.
The pain, the blinding lights, the thundering sounds in their ears were all too terrible for the Lucky population to endure.
During this time of horror above ground, the Lost were living below the surface.
Watching the scene unfold on cameras and biding their time for when they could once again regain control of the Earth from the childish Lucky.
The fortunate individuals understood they had to take action, no matter what, in order to stop the pain.

Even though they were filled with hatred for the original recipients of the miracle medication, they also had some compassion that remained which didn't allow them to let other creatures endure prolonged suffering.
It was once again a case of the haves and have nots.
Only instead of money or wealth as in the previous world order, it was life or death.
The Lost decided they must do something they never thought they would.
They must give their proven, more effective miracle medicine to all of the Lucky ones.
So they did.
Once more, the outcomes were immediate.
The pain would come to an end.
But not as the Lost imagined it would, with a cure for the Lucky and renewed immortality.
But with a pop and bang and puff of smoke as the Lucky simply vanished off the face of the Earth.
Following Lucky's death, the remaining Lost colonies started establishing their own governments and planning their next steps.
They agreed that they couldn't let the same errors from their previous civilization happen again.
They selected the most skilled and intelligent individuals from the last remaining colonies.
These people began to work on a new and improved drug for immortality in the event the same situation were to strike them that had been inflicted upon the Lucky.
Once more, they achieved their goals.

However, the effort of developing this medicine had a negative impact on the mental and physical health of the remaining individuals. As a result, they decided to construct a space residence where they could focus on creating their next revolutionary medication in a calm and tranquil environment.

He slunk down in his office chair.
I thought I was #1 Dad., he mumbled.
He glanced a few cubicles down and saw Mark McDonald's mug read #409,908,100 which made John feel a bit better.
'I'm still the  best in this office,' he said to himself.
But then he glanced in the other direction and saw that Larry Lyle's mug still read '#1 Dad.'
Larry grinned happily as John's face transformed into a look of envy.
Larry, meanwhile, was gleowng.

John smiled as he gazed at the mug he was holding.
The legend '#1' was affixed to piece of cardboard glued onto the mug.
When Larry returned, his mug was gone.
Knowingly, he walks over to Larry and said 'Where's my mug....mug?'
Larry pulled it out of his bottom drawer.

'World's #1 Dad,' it read.
It's hard to say who was more surprised.

However, being critical to the news is a bad trait because it will cause restlessness in the society.

Thus, we should be aware of our surroundings and refrain from being judgmental.
Thus,all people should keep up with the news to some extent, but they shouldn't get criticism towards it.

To sum it up, we should know what is going on in the world by keeping up with the news, but we should not get critical of it just because we think differently from what is reported.

By doing so, you can prevent yourself from being critical by avoiding information that is biased.
'Do you have any idea how wealthy you all could be living inside all of that uranium?'
The pigs knew the uranium was no longer radioactive, but it was still really strong and they were formulating an idea in their little piggy minds.
You see, the little pigs had lived together for so long, they now thought as one brain.
The plot developing, was to get all of the big, bad wolves from the entire world into one place.
That place being their uranium fortress.
The wolves were unaware, but the little pigs had been keeping an eye on them.
The pigs knew of the wealth the wolves had accumulated from eating weaker animals and then taking their fortunes for their own use.
This angered the pigs, and many small animal all over the globe.
The idea the pigs were going to set into motion was to make the uranium home appear to be an exclusive, super expensive resort that catered only to wolves.
The would advertise all sorts of things to attract the wolves to the home.
Since most advertising is based on false promises, the pigs felt no guilt in stretching the truth to lure the savage creatures to the home.
Only the small pigs were aware of the dangerous snare they were arranging.
The home was fortified even more, making it impossible to escape once the alarms and traps had been set.
The invitations to an exclusive, posh, wolves only resort were sent out to every wolf who had amassed great fortune at the expense of others.
Over the next week, the wolves began to arrive.
Paying what constituted their entire fortune the wolves were admitted to the exclusive 'spa' for a once in a lifetime experience.
Or as the pigs later told in their tales of this exploit, an end of a lifetime experience.
The wolves were led to their accommodations and settled in, getting ready to relax.
They were fed luscious meals, made from fake meat, and given all the treatment royalty would expect.
When the last wolf of great wealth and power finally arrived, the terminal stages of the plan were set in motion.
The pigs all left the fortress quietly in the dark of night.
The uranium tomb was locked and secured.
The pigs went back home and gave most of their earning to their mother and friends.
The wolves were left to take care of themselves.
They awoke to find no pigs, no food, and no way out.
As they say, it's a wolf eat wolf world in a uranium strong hold.
When you were young, your parents worried whenever you stepped outside to play with friends.
Would they be able to help you in time should you get stung by a bee, was a common worry that plagued them during your youth.
You looked around, but could not see anyone.
The field you were standing on were empty, the only sight was the grass you were standing on under the clear blue sky above.
Once again you heard a voice speak amongst the silence, 'Your Majesty, I await your orders.'
You look down, and see a little bee, no larger than a thumb, looking up at you from your shoulder.
You feel shocked, not only has a bee landed on your shoulder, but it has talked to you as if you were royalty.
You feel as if you are in a dream, but the bright sun shining on your skin makes it clear that you are wide awake.
You speak out loud, ' Who are you?
', in a confused tone of voice.
The small bee responds, 'I am dedicated to serving you, Your Highness. I am your faithful servant.'
'Surely you have a name,' you replied back to the bee claiming to be your servant.
I know, but I am not permitted to say it, Your Highness.
You ponder in your head why speaking their name would not be allowed, but decide against it.
You then speak, ' Are their others who wish to serve as my servants?'
The little bee replies, 'Yes, Your Majesty, there are many who wish to serve you, but I am the first to arrive,.'
Your head begins to fill with many racing thoughts, of what you can do with hundreds, maybe thousands of servants at your command.
You then proclaim, 'Tell them to arrive to my quarters, for it shall be their new home.'
As the tiny bee takes flight, a sense of happiness washes over you, as if you have achieved a long-awaited desire.
You would have companionship, and will overcome your fear of being stung.
When once bees were a source of fear due to your allergies, your loyal servants would not sting you out of respect for you.
As you make your way back to your room, you are greeted by a large group of bees, all of them smiling.
As their queen, they expect commands to ensure your protection, and you would be happy to be their queen as long as they protect you.
From that moment on you would be royalty, a human commanding hundreds of loyal bees, and in time you would forget that you were ever allergic to bees.
For the bees that served you would protect you from other foreign bees, and you would be safe from ever being stung in your entire life.

eople were losing their minds - everywhere we went, we would see people screaming at one another,: men fighting with their wives, kids in tears, brothers getting up in arms about long-forgotten sibling disputes.

Before the main feature starts there are some previews of other things.
One of the options is a movie about a man who has come back to life as a fly.
You watch with little interest until you realize that the man is you.
You wonder what's going on, were you really a fly in a past life?
Or, even worse, is this your fate for the future?!
The movie is lighthearted in tone, but it conveys an important message.
This is the life you could have lived if you had decided to do something very bad in a previous life.
Luckily you made the right choice and avoided the life of a fly.
Another preview begins to play.
It is about a man who has come back to life in the form of a dog.
You wonder if, again, this dog was you.
Sure enough this is a life you could have had in a previous reincarnation.
Had you not been bold and followed your dreams you would have been this dog in your last life.
Not as bad as being a fly, perhaps, but still not great.
Another preview plays.
This time you are shown a being of great power living a life of pure joy.
You learn that this is the life you could have had if you had fulfilled all of your potential in your previous lives.
You are told that you won't actually be seeing your next life as that life is up to you to live.
The reason you were brought here is to understand the ramifications that your actions have on your upcoming reincarnations.
But, they are being kept secret from the world.
Word is starting to filter out, a leak here a leak there, just rumors, no knows what to believe.
Still, a consensus is starting to form around a single idea, and you are grateful you didn't get the drug.
The truth seems to be that  sixty years after they took the drug they start to lose their minds, and end up in a vegetative state.
It's like Alzheimer's overnight.
The people that took the trial drug, before FDA approval all seem to be exhibiting this zombie like state.
And now this is the destiny for everyone that was given it before their twenty-eighth birthday.
We, the 'Lost Generation', have age, but we don't have this doom hanging over us.
In fact because of our status we have been cared for by those that did get the drug, we get the best health care, the best medicines, the best treatments, since those others feel a guilt towards us.
So, it's not so bad being a Lost Generation, most of us feel as if we are still in our forties.
But, the world is doomed, those that care for us will soon be unable to take care of themselves, and we are in no position to repopulate the world.
This is truly the end of man kind, and we brought it on ourselves.
We should make an effort to enjoy the remaining time we have.
It's a health issue, and schools need to be responsible for the health of the children they are charged with supervising.
Period poverty is a significant problem that exists.
Young women need to be protected from the social stigma of poverty.
Lack of access to period products is a public health concern.
Not having the necessary items for self care is both physically harmful and emotionally stressful.
It puts an undo burden on young women to allow them to go through a day at school without what they need to take care of themselves.
There is no opportunity for a child to better their own situation.
These young people are expected to attend school, and they need all of the necessary supplies to do that in a healthy, safe and comfortable way.
When the parents can't afford lunch, most school systems, who can afford it, provide lunch for the student.
The same principle needs to apply to young women and girls who may need sanitary supplies, and cannot afford them.
Resources are very limited in many school districts and I empathize with their plight, but forcing children to attend school all day without making sure they have adequate supplies is simply wrong.
It shouldn't matter what gender the student is, or what the need is.
If there is a need, the school needs to be accountable for making sure that the need is met.
I hope that resources become easier to come by for these schools but until then, there can be no excuses made.
Young women need to be provided with everything they need to attend school and learn, without having to worry about basic needs.
The 92nd pig, also known as 'Arthur' replied from behind his asbestos suit 'You can huff and puff all you want and you will probably end up with radiation poisoning!'
Because the wolf was a wolf, it was not easily convinced otherwise.
He left for a bit, but before long he was back with an army of cockroaches.
The wolf was well read and knew that radiation does not effect cockroaches, so he called in a favor with a roach wrangler friend of his to lend him a couple of thousand.
The wolf watched with glee as the roach patrol stormed Arthur's house covering the windows and door and crawling between the cracks.
The roaches were on him in a flash and Arthur was soon covered in roaches.
It was only a matter of time, now.
The screams were muffled at first because of Arthur's protective suit, then they got louder as he removed the helmet to let the roaches that had crawled into the suit out.
Unfortunately, this gave the roaches even more of an opening.
Terrified and repulsed, Arthur bolted for the door and shouldered his way through it.
He was half in and half out of his protective suit now and was rolling on the ground trying to get the roaches off of him.
The wolf could hardly contain his laughter.
Arthur was a total disaster.
He finally got the last of the roaches off of him and the wolf came over and gathered the roaches up using the attractant that his wrangler friend gave him.
He looked over at Arthur and winked.
'You thought you had me beat didn't you, pig?'
Arthur told him, "You will face consequences for this."
'Not until you pay up first!
Give me my winnings!'
Arthur let out a short grunt and handed over the fifty dollars that the wolf won in the bet.
'Thank you kindly' the wolf said boastfully as he put the money into his shirt pocket.
Don't worry little pig, your brothers all lost their bets, too except for pig number 73.
He made his house out of duct tape and I am still trying to figure out how to get into it!'
'So long, number 92!'
The wolf said as he sauntered off to see if he could find pig number 93 and win yet another bet.
Today was the day.
He and Valarie had been dating for almost a year.
Well, this time around.
This was the 4th time they dated, but all of the other times they had crashed and burned after less than 8 months.
So he was certain that this was the right face.
He had everything planned in advance.
He bought a ring, made the dinner reservations, and rented out the observation deck of her favorite city viewing spot.
It was hard being a shapeshifter.
Once you started changing, even just once, there was so much to keep track of, and so much work to do to create a new 'you'.
It was a lot of work to keep track of all the details of your life, and to make sure that you didn't leave any evidence of your past, while still maintaining a legal identity.
Not that his current one was technically 'legal'.
He was born in a small Midwest town and was just an average person until he was involved in a car accident.
They had expected horrible scarring, and were surprised there was none.
But he didn't look like he had either.
In fact, he suddenly grew 3 inches, and looked and awful like the popular actor of the time, the one all the girls in his class had been gushing over.
At first he thought he had the best luck, but then he realized the changes just freaked every one out.
He was an oddity and had to depart from the city.
One day a woman he was interested in told him she preferred brunettes.
When he woke up the next morning his hair color was different, and there were changes to his face.
And that's when he knew.
He could control this.
Which came in handy when he met Valarie.
They dated for about 3 months the first time, then she broke up with him when he flirted with another woman.
He realized his mistake, but she just wouldn't take him back.
So he changed.
He wasn't really certain why the other times he dated her didn't work out.
It could be that he had a reputation for being a ladies' man while she did not.
He didn't cheat, but who doesn't like attention?
But this time, it seemed like she accepted him for what he was, and this time he was going to get to marry her.
Dinner was strangely tense, which he had not been expected.
He asked about her day, but all she would say was that she had an extra long session with her therapist, and they could talk about it later.
He thought that was weird, but they were in a restaurant; maybe she didn't want to get emotional there?
He had eagerly anticipated this evening for a while, and he was committed to making it memorable.
They went to the observation deck, and if anything the atmosphere got even more intense.
She appeared angry with him, causing him to become annoyed.
He was about to tell her she was ruining the moment, when she turned to him.
'I've been talking to my therapist for months now about my past relationships.
She's helped me see that I keep dating the same kind of man.
She has been making me realize that I continue to date you.
He recoiled in shock, suddenly fearful.
No one could know his secret, not even her, it was too dangerous.
SHe looked away from him, holding the railing as she looked out over the city.
He didn't want to do it, but he had to.
He got ready to push her.
'Well, not literally you, but your type.
And it just isn't good for me.
So, I'm sorry, but this is goodbye.'
He stopped just before pushing her, relieved for a moment.
Then angry again, fists clenched, just what did he have to be to keep her?
Just as he was about to shove her, he suddenly felt a hand on his shoulder.
'You're a good man and you deserve better.
I'm going to leave and start a new life somewhere else, a whole new me.
I wish the best for you.'
And with that he finally felt shame.
He was the one who had been deceiving her, and she called him a good man.
He let her go, and decided that this was it.
He would keep this face and identity, but make a new life for himself, without her.
He took the ring box out of his pocket, left it on a table, and walked away.
At the root of this belief is the fact that they are risking their health and thus their future by participating in high-risk sports like football.
Even if a college athlete avoids injury during their playing years, they may still suffer long-lasting physical issues that prevent them from pursuing alternative careers.
The concussion syndrome linked to contact sports like football is a prime example.
College athletics has become a huge money machine.
Big sports program schools have been willing and have paid top dollar for a few select athletes so that is not going to change.
College athletes deserve the chance to be compensated for their efforts.
The way to resolve this is to make college sports just that college sports.
The focus of a college should be education, sports is what is done in free time from studies.
After all, there is no college curriculum for 'pro football player', no degrees are offered for 'professional athlete'.
College sports were never intended to be a source of long-term employment.
For those whose focus is a career in professional sports there should be a junior league much as baseball has the minor leagues.
Education should be provided in the areas that would most benefit a professional athlete, like money management, etc.
Colleges with big sports programs would protest this mightily but then they need to refocus their sight on providing an excellent education for all their students.
You look at the bee for a moment.
You realize that your entire life, you've been lied to.
'You're saying I'm the Queen of Bees?'
you ask.
'Yes Your Majesty,' it replies.
'So, I'm like some spiritual force that controls all bees reincarnated into a human body?'
you continue.
'Yes, your majesty'Your eyes grow flat, dangerous.
'And the allergies?'
The bee gazes at you with a sense of sympathy in its eyes.
'A ruse Your Majesty.'
You pause for a moment, then ask another question.
'And my mother?'
The bee's eyes hang in shame.
You nod.
'Of course, she's not really my mother.'
You think about the situation for a bit, the web of lies, the complexities of it all.
You decide you don't really care.
'So, bottom line is that I now control an army of bees who will do whatever I wish?'
'Indeed, Your Majesty, that is accurate.'
You nod.
'All right, let's see my army.'
You snap your fingers.
The noise is so deafening that it seems like it has been heard by everyone in the world.
Immediately, bees are all around you.
You have what you've wanted your whole life now, power.
'Let's start with 'Mom.'
You open the door, and the bees rush in to sting her.
You follow them, and get a moment to savor her dying screams before the bees finish her off.
After that is the handyman, since he's handy.
Then, a trip to the medical center, to visit the doctor who told you were allergic to bees.
After a long day of bee murder, you decide to go to your room and relax.
Tomorrow will be an interesting day at school, you're sure.
That pretty girl in 4th period will pay for the names she called you.
And the bully who took your lunch money every day for an entire year?
He'll be eating a diet of bee venom, and you hope he enjoys it.
Before you go to bed, the bee starts babbling about some prophecy, but you ignore it.
You're not here to fulfill some mystical destiny.
You're here to make the entire world kneel before the power of the Queen of Bees.
This is an essential life skill that is often overlooked during education.
The most valuable lesson I have gained from my education is the ability to critically analyze information.
I have developed the skills to analyze a problem, devise a solution, and assess its effectiveness.
Critical thinking is a method that is taught specifically in higher education for certain professions, such as healthcare professionals.
However, it is not commonly taught.
I believe that teaching critical thinking skills at a young age in schools is important.
Ideally this would be taught in a small classroom size setting, where the teacher can work with each student individually.
This would allow the implementation of a more hands-on approach to learning in all subject areas.
IAnother way to increase critical thinking in early childhood education is by homeschooling.
Homeschooling permits parents to customize the curriculum based on the child's individual needs.
Also, the child participates in elements of everyday life at home with an adult , which allows them to learn how to think critically in a more natural setting.
By shadowing adults as they work through everyday problems and problem solving, children are able to learn how to think critically in a more natural setting.
This allows for a smoother transition into higher education and working age.
I promote and support any form of teaching that allows for more hands-on learning.
I think the benefits are enormous and will improve the lives of students.

The first stirrings of its presence are felt in the small town of Little Haven,  a place where a handful of survivors huddle together, hoping to escape the notice of the alien attackers.
It manifests itself with the arrival of a mysterious stranger, a man who appears to be human but who possesses powers far beyond those of any human mage.
He begins to guide the survivors in the practice of magic, which has begun to manifest in some of them as a result of the aliens' attack, and the resulting diminishment in the human population.
Before long , the survivors begin to believe that their only hope for survival lies in the mastery of magic.

Under the leadership of the mysterious stranger, the survivors begin to explore the nature of the power they possess, and the means by which they can use it to defend themselves against the alien invaders.
They defend the town against a small alien attack, wielding magic as a weapon for the first time.
Before long, they have begun to launch small counterattacks against the aliens with increasing degrees of success.
However, they notice something disturbing.
The world around them appears to undergo noticeable changes as they employ more magic.
The trees, the animals, are becoming altered in not-so-subtle ways into things they can't recognize.
One of the villagers, Jonas, begins to notice that his wife is changing, as well.
She's become mercurial, speaking in a language that's impossible for him to understand at times, though the stranger seems to understand her perfectly.
Jonas confronts the stranger, demanding to know what's happening to his wife.
The stranger explains that the magic they're using is causing a fundamental change in the nature of the world, and that it's a change that will affect them all.
He reveals that he is not a human, but an alien, and that his people have been using magic for thousands of years.
He tells Jonas that long ago, they used magic to transform themselves into beings that could lave their planet, which was dying.
He had landed on earth eons ago, and had dominated the development of early man, but as the mana faded, he had been forced to retreat into a form of hibernation.
Jonas is uneasy about what these changes will entail, and what the future for humanity will be, but the stranger points to his wife.
Would you rather know her as this, and she know you as you will become?'
He then points to the graveyard.
Or is this your preference?'
Jonas goes away, and spend the night in thought.
The next day, he has decided not to inform the other townsfolk about what he knows.
They grow stronger, and lead the growing rebellion against the alien conquerors.
Before long, it is clear that they will eventually win this war.
But will anything be left of humanity to celebrate that victory?
If college athletes are paid, they will be more concerned about the money than the game or the team.
Moreover, compensating college athletes increases the likelihood of cheating.
Fairness of the game is therefore jeopardized.
In addition, if college athletes are paid, they will be more likely to leave school early.
College athletes are expected to focus on their academic studies rather than pursuing a career as professional athletes.
Their first priority should be the academic performance.
Being paid to pay sports will distract the students from focusing on their academic, thus ruining the ultimate purpose of attending college.
Providing monetary compensation to players gives them a false interpretation that sports are linked to monetary compensation.
The meaning of sportsmanship would thus be lost.
Due to these downsides in providing monetary compensation to players, I think that athletes should not be paid monetary compensation.
I'm a gay person and I like to watch a lot of TV and Movies and media content.

Many gay characters are well done and interesting, but there are some, particularly in old shows from the 1970s and before when treatment of gay persons, even the mention of them, makes them seem like pariahs.
Like they don't matter or worse like they are simply bad or villains because of their sexual identity.
I find, when people are snickering about how 'gay' someone seems or how they are 'queer' or 'Nancies'... it's offensive.
There are many classic TV and Movie portrayals where this is seen.
One older Movie I recently watched, which was, during it's time, considered popular was the Movie Thunderbolt and Lightfoot, with Clint Eastwood and Jeff Bridges.
Allusions to one or more characters portraying or 'making the move' on another character were seen derisively, and as a horror.
I find this demeaning and troubling.
When watching shows like this I DO cringe.
I realize it's from a time gone by, and things have changed, but they haven't changed THAT much.
I've seen other older shows or movies where this sort of thing was present and it troubled me, but the show or movie was well done otherwise.
When this happens I REALLY cringe.
It elevates how important the medium is or show and that allows for the negation of a whole class of people.
I see this sort of treatment all the time in real life today, which makes watching something like this all the more irritating and cringe worthy.
There are times I will switch something like this off.
Opting for another show, or nothing instead.
It makes me feel less than, and I worry that even reshowing something like this will make young people watching it think it's ok to do that in real life.
That is not acceptable.
I want to scream, but who do I scream to?
Does anyone care any more?
I DO like that many gay writers and directors, such as Ryan Murphy, give strong and varied gay roles to actors, and portray interesting story lines that include all types of people.
Focusing in on what different people do, in different situations instead of pigeonholing everyone.
I would like to see this.
I opt for these stronger choices, things that make me feel like I matter.
I want to live in today, making gay people normal, allowing for a space for everyone, and for everyone to feel safe.
So, if you have a show or movie with stereotypical portrayals of gay people... simply switch it off, and opt for something that also makes YOU a better person.
I believe that the opportunity to play in front of cheering fans, training with a professional program and team,  and the chance to get a college education is enough.
I think that compensating college athletes would have a negative impact on college sports.
I think that compensating college athletes would lead to colleges competing for the best players through financial means.
Colleges would have to overpay for a handful of athletes, and have to cut funding for other activities.
There would be no 'underdog with a chance to win', no dark horses, just the haves, and the have-nots.
We'd have a few super-programs who dominated everything due to their excessive cash-bought top talent.
The money would go to a select few athletes, leaving the rest of the team with less.
In a society already dominated by money, we'd just be allowing another thing to become 'pay-to-win'.
IPying college athletes would hurt the broader community of student-athletes, universities, fans and alumni.
Rural and poorer schools would have losing teams, harming the opportunities for motivation and success of some students.
There would be inequality in payment, and inequality in opportunity.
The NCAA operates as a not-for-profit entity.
It is a group of schools, and the athletes are members of that group.
It returns all of its profits to the schools and the furthering of athletic programs.
It works to keep schools a place of learning, not a place of money and business.
I think that the NCAA is a fantastic institution, and I think it should remain as it is.
We should keep money and greed from destroying a good system.
There is this odor that certain people exude.
It's both familiar as well as off-putting.
You notice the smell more often in large crowds and it's becoming troubling enough that you've begun to stay home.
You don't mind much, you've lived a long life.
It's one thing to see your former college friends brag about their lives on social media, never having changed their looks.
Seeing someone on the subway who resembles your old best friend, only to the realize they have the familiar scent of decay, is a different experience altogether.
You hide your face as others in the subway hear your gasp.
You realize that you are the only person in that packed subway who has aged.
The smell intensifies, making you gag.
You hide your face, tuck it into your scarf, breathing in the scent of your lotion.
You try to tell yourself that you are detecting your own breath, but the scent remains present.
You exit the car at the next stop, despite it being 3 exits from home.
The smell lingers in your nose as you rush home.
You enter the house and lock the door, rushing towards your master bathroom only to be taken aback when you step foot in your bedroom.
A man is standing there, gazing in your direction.
The scent is present.
You fall to the ground, placing a hand over your mouth as you start to gag.
'Why?!'
you ask, but you know the answer already.
'Vanity' the man says.
'Vanity and narcissism are rotting people at their core, rotting their life away from the inside out'You fall forward, still retching as the man approaches you.
'But, I've lived a good life, why am I the one to suffer and have to stay locked up inside to avoid the rot?'
you ask'You're not the one suffering' he says.
'We all are.'
At this point you realize that you can't live this way.
You are dying a regular death.
A death that was once natural.
The others?
They are dying unnaturally and their vanity makes it so that they will never even know.
You turn back towards the man and see a syringe on the bed beside him.
You stand up and grab the man by his neck.
'Why are you making me do this?!'
you cry.
'I'm not making you do anything, I'm just giving you the option now that you know the truth' the man replies.
Therefore, you grab a needle and summon your remaining bravery.
It's this or never leaving home again, dying alone in pain without anyone knowing or dying now.
You choose now and jab the needle into your neck.
The smell of rose scented lotion wafts past you and you smile as your body relaxes.
It's over.
Compared to a human that can use their mind to assess the best action while being beaten, an animial can not easily escape a raging human.
Animals can not do wrong in a moral sense.
Humans, on the other hand, are flawed.

There is, however, no reason ever, to harm either man or beast.
On the contrary, any steps to reduce suffering, whether human or nonhuman, should be taken.
It is wrong to beat a living being.
In fact, in America, this is referred to as assault and is against the law.
The assailant can be fined and jailed.
So, hurting others is both lawless and immoral.
I think it is normal to have a disparity in the amount of concern for a suffering animal or person.
It would be wrong if a person chose to save an animal over a human.
People are higher beings, spiritually.
They are higher on the food chain and the moral chain, if there is such a thing.
Animals and humans are not on the same level.
Ultimately, doing deliberate harm is wrong and unnecessary.
I do not believe in such violence.
Although over time due to limited food they would pass away from starvation, in the end there remained 20 little pigs that survived.
When they were old enough, the mother pig sent them away to find new homes for themselves, and hopefully start a family.
They would try to survive in a harsh world with the homes they would build, out of any materials that they could find.
Many found that there homes could not withstand the forces of nature or the attacks of predators, and died soon after.
Only one would survive to live to adulthood, the last and youngest of the 20 little pigs.
However, unlike his siblings who had also built houses sturdy enough to stand against harsh winds and natural disasters, the 20th little pig had devised a way to avoid predators.
He had built a massive underground bunker, with a maze of tunnels that he could use to escape from any predator should they try to break into his house.
The bunker was well hidden, fortified, and stocked, able to sustain him if the predators were to break into his above home.
He would often leave his house unlocked at night, while he slept underground in his bunker, to fool predators into thinking the home was already abandoned.
Sure enough, predators eventually gave up on the house of the 20th little pig.
The 20th little pig was able to live a long life free from the threat of predators, and when he died he left his home to his children.
They would keep his legacy alive, and continue to live in the house, and the bunker, that he had built.
For unlike his siblings, he would still be alive like his descendants, who expanded his underground bunker.
They would form a community of pigs, who would call themselves, 'The Bunker Pigs', living primarily underground where no predators could catch them.
She meets him again, after he follows her to a bar.
He is charming.
The process starts again.
She's dating him again.
He comes over to her house for dinner one night.
She has everything prepared very nicely.
They enjoy their dinner.
She inquires if he would be interested in having some dessert.
He accepts and they sit out on the balcony, having dessert and wine.
He continuously expresses his gratitude towards her.
She finds this odd, because they really don't know each other that well yet.
She notices that she is beginning to feel uneasy.
There is something eerily familiar about the scene.
She gazes into his eyes and sees a single desire: hunger.
She's seen that hunger before.
Her last boyfriend had it too.
Now she sees it in this man and she suddenly realizes that she has somehow fallen for the same trap again.
She has developed feelings for the man without a face, who cannot exist as a genuine or authentic person.
She doesn't realize that he is a shapeshifter, but she knows that she's seen this exact scene play out before.
It didn't go well before and she has no reason to believe that it will go well this time.
Actually, she is convinced that it will not happen.
She tells him that she's got a headache and would like him to leave.
He seems startled by this.
He inquires if she is ending their relationship.
She tells him that they barely know each other, that there is no relationship to end.
He looks so puzzled, she is taken back.
She understands that he is unaware of what she is saying.
It is right then that she begins to suspect that something deeper is going on.
She doesn't understand it, but she's starting to come to the realization that he is, in fact, the same man she just broke up with.
She suspects that he is the same man she's broken up with many times.
The shocking awareness that she keeps dating the same person repeatedly is overwhelming.
She asks him to leave, again.
This time, he begs her not to ask him to go away.
He begins weeping.
She is stunned by what is going on.
She has witnessed this performance previously.
She walks to the door, opens it, and curtly says, 'goodnight.'
He leaves, but never takes his eyes off of her.
She spins around with a hint of fear.
Later that night she searches the internet for clues about what was going on with him.
She is shocked to find that many women have had this same experience.
She reads about beings that can change form and believes deep down that this is who she has been seeing.
The woman joins the foreign legion and ships off, later that week.
She never dates anyone again.

COVID is a great time for kids to disconnect from their screens and reconnect with their families.
This is possibly the only time in history when this opportunity will exist, since COVID has required parents to stay home from work and work remotely on a full-time basis.
Honestly, under what other circumstances could we expect to have the entire family home together for an extended period of time?

There are so many parents who are able to make homemade dinners now, eat with their kids, and play family board games at night after a day of working from home, when they would really not be able to do so if they were still commuting in rush hour traffic on a daily basis going into the office.
I think that this is a great time to take advantage of the opportunity to reconnect with our kids, and to get them off their screens fas much as possible.
It'd just be so unfortunate to allow this period of time to be filled with screen time.
Do we really want America's youth to just be totally dependent on their screens for entertainment, socialization and connection?
It's frankly just concerning...
If you've ever seen the Social Network documentary on Netflix then you know what I'm talking about.

That documentary really put me on the edge of my seat, because it told the gripping story of some kids who were so sucked into their phones and social media accounts that they practically lost all sense of self and eventually even lost a grip on reality!
Moreover, screens are just inherently addictive.
I know this because I'm a recovering addict myself.
I have been so plugged into my phone before that I was unable to have a conversation with my own husband.
That was a scary place to be, and I'm so glad that I'm not there anymore.
I am grateful to be able to spend time with my children and have meaningful conversations with my husband.
I would never want my kids to be in that place, and I think that it's important to be aware of the addictive nature of screens.
So truly, I think that we should be worried about excessive screen use during COVID.
I have friends who allow their kids to watch TV all day, and I think that's a really bad idea.
My friends justify it because they say that their kids are watching educational shows.
But can we really expect that kids will be able to tell the difference between educational and non-educational shows?
I mean, even the supposedly educational shows are still filled with commercials for junk food and toys.
And even the supposedly educational shows can still feature inappropriate content.
For example, I was watching a show with my kids the other day, and I noticed that one of the characters was drinking alcohol.
And that show is supposed to be educational?
I just couldn't believe it.
In conclusion, kids should absolutely be off their screens during COVID.
We've always been so hurried and rushed with our lives up to this point and this is a really nice chance to just level set and reset as a family without screens.

The benefits of listening to an audiobook, is that the reader can engage with a story at a good pace.
Some people are not as fast as readers as others, and notably may struggle to read depending on the contents of the story.
Some people prefer to listen to a book while they are busy with their daily activities, rather than holding a physical book.
Listening is seen as a passive ability, as many are skilled at doing so while they engage in other activities such as driving, or even while exercising.

Listening also has the benefit of engaging a person into the setting of the story, as a good audiobook narrator is skilled at voicing the characters and also at setting the background and surroundings facing the characters.
Reading, while more active and requiring more concentration than listening, can be a more involved and personal activity than listening.
Readers can control their pace, and even take notes on areas in the book that they may wish to look into more or take further time to understand.
They can go back on what they read to see the characters under new contexts and information.
A reader, can also dictate how a character sounds, as listening to an audiobook sets that choice for the listener, who may or may not agree with the narrator's choice.
In my opinion, I prefer reading over listening to an audiobook.

While good audiobook narrators can add to the experience of a book, they are not able to be the definite choice for the author's characters, much less how I can picture the characters in their tone, dialect, and even inflection.

For me to get immersed, I have to chose my own pace for engaging in the story, taking the time to pause the story if I want to think more in depth about what has happened, or to connect it with other thoughts I may have.
An audiobook while it can be paused, will always move a constant pace dictated by the narrator.
Sometimes, I may show excitement or a strong interest to continue reading into the plot, reading faster to see what happens next to the characters.
Other times, I slow down to absorb all the information of the book's pages, to better understand what happens next in the book.
Ultimately I enjoy being able to address the story in ways that an audiobook cannot offer based on the strengths and weaknesses of both mediums.

One day you awake to find yourself in a mysterious room, that isn't like your typical bedroom.
In fact, the room is better furnished and seems much more expensive than the items you own.
The massive flat screen in front of you is new, and you wonder how much it could have cost, much less how you could ever afford it on your personal income.
Turning to your right you see a bathroom, and you get out of bed to examine this luxurious bathroom.
The bathroom, like the bedroom is much more elegant than your utilitarian restroom, having a much more massive shower with its own tub.
You glance at the mirror to inspect yourself, and you are shocked at what you see.
Staring in front of the mirror is none other than famous actor Matt Damon.
You start to consider the possibility that this may just be a dream, leading to some confusion.
There is no logical way you could be Matt Damon, or even controlling his body.
You were just an average person, who had an average life with an average job at the local hospital, not some renowned actor that earns millions per movie.
All of a sudden, the bathroom door swings open, revealing your wife, Luciana.
She wonders what is going on, as you normally do not spend so much time in the rest room inspecting yourself.
You attempt to clarify the situation and describe how you transformed into Matt Damon, but she simply stares at you in disbelief with a bewildered expression.
She otherwise passes it off as an elaborate joke you are making, and suggests that you get ready to go to work.
Work, you ponder, it surely meant a film shoot, and not your usual job at the hospital.
Your mind was racing trying to piece together this new reality you were thrust into, and you couldn't help but think that your were way over your head.
Grabbing Matt Damon's smart phone, you noticed a missed call, who left a voicemail.
The message was from your agent, Alex saying to get to the film shoot in about an hour as you are needed for an important shot.
You then panic, as you get the address to the film set, and you head out.
You drive in a car that you don't recognize, and get to the set on time.
There everyone seems relived to see you arrive, and they thrust you onto the set.
You are informed that your role in this film is crucial and the production company cannot delay any further.
You are then given little time to rehearse, and filming begins almost immediately.
The performance you give feels mediocre to you, but the director and the rest of the crew find it satisfactory.
The assure you that they will edit it to be much more engaging before it releases in films.
You leave the set, and spend the rest of your day at Matt Damon's home.
The next morning you wake up and head to the bathroom to shower.
You realize you are back in your old body, and that you are no longer Matt Damon.
Relieved, you realized that it was all an elaborate, but interesting dream you had.
That is until you ended up watching the latest Matt Damon film that you were in, and noticed the scene you acted in.
Seeing the way Matt Damon moved their hands during the scene made you realize it was you controlling his body during that shoot, and that it wasn't a dream you had.
For one day in your life, you were att Damon., and the thought of such filled you with such as sense of pride even if no one else would ever believe you.

ads and tampons are similar to toilet paper, soap, Band-Aids and other products that are already provided in schools because they basic necessity.
Pads and tampons are a necessity for women, especially when they experience period poverty.
Period poverty refers to the inadequate access to menstrual products for individuals who menstruate.
Period poverty is a significant problem that impacts females globally.
A United Nations study found that over 800 million women and girls globally do not have access to feminine hygiene products.
This presents a significant issue as it can result in health complications like infections, reproductive tract infections, and cervical cancer.
It can also adversely affect the mental health of women and girls because their moods change easily during their periods.
Pads and tampons are essential items, not indulgences.
The US government has already implemented measures to assist women and girls facing period poverty.
For instance, the US government has been supplying feminine hygiene products to females at refugee camps.
As a conclusion, I think that schools should provide free pads and tampons to female students with a quota restriction.

We didn't continue to date, but we continued to talk.
We found that our friendship was missing from our lives, even though we were completely unaware of its possibility before meeting on a dating app.
Neither of us would have thought to reach out or see the other person, in any other context, even though we lived in the same place and had similar interests.
Dating apps have enabled me to make a new acquaintance who has likely had a more profound influence on my life than many of my romantic partners.
I find a lot of upside to dating apps, and very few downsides.
Most of the downside to the apps would be if a person is very impatient, and doesn't feel comfortable around other people.
These apps only really require one thing of users, something that all participants need to have in common, and that is the ability to keep an open mind and be patient with oneself and others.
This is something that not everyone knows how to do, but once it is learned, it leads to new social connections with people, which can lead to a happier life.
I recommend that everyone who is looking to meet new people try a dating app, at least once.

In addition, they are helpful for people who are more time constrained than others, who do not possess the time or energy to read or, even for those that find it is easier and more convenient to listen to an audio book than to read the same book.
Those are all the advantages present in audiobooks, but if one wants to go further, there are some smaller but none-the-less important advantages.
For audiobooks are also more accessible by those who are illiterate as well as those who cannot read as fast as is required to follow along with a print book.
They are a good way for people to entertain and occupy themselves, and potentially learn more about a topic.
More people can hear an audiobook at a given time, which can open up discussion and potential further engagement with one another.
And most importantly, it is a gateway to literature for those who may not have access to the written word, or who might not enjoy reading as much.
For audiobooks need not to compete with the concept of reading, for they are a good complement for it that is accessible and available to many.
Just as audiobooks have advantages that worth considering, so do print books.
When reading, a person can set their own pace and decide for themselves how long to spend with the book, not having to worry about listening time.

In addition, they can become more invested in the literature, as reading makes the person more able to picture the events of the story, and even gives the reader greater input in how the story is read, as audiobooks have set narrators that voice the characters and events of the story.
For me, these are appealing benefits that draws me more to reading, than to listening to an audiobook.
That isn't to say as mentioned I would discourage the use of audiobooks for myself nor for others, just that if given the choice and time, I would find reading more enjoyable.
That is the critical aspect of both audiobooks and written literature, that ideally both should be available as a choice for people all around the world.
They both provides benefits and drawbacks that the other lacks, and I feel they can coexist without competition.
I think the two main choices will boil down to the preferences of the user, and they ultimately have to decide which works best for them at any given point in their life.

Surely avoiding this charade does not make someone a bad citizen.
Simply by being attentive and engaged with our communities, we can help ensure that our citizens stay well-informed.
But watching all of the negative commentary embedded within the news can actually hurt communities by deepening an already existing political divide.
Engaging with current event can be more helpful on a local level, for example if you are helping feed people in your community because of a tragedy.
This, also, can be done simply by paying attention and does not have to involve consuming the news.
All in all, I'd say people shouldn't be worried about not keeping up with the news.

We aren't bad citizens if we don't keep up with the news.

A sport is a business, and its purpose is to make money, pure and simple.
A sport gets played because it makes money for the owners and players.
Nowhere in the calculation of profit does it consider the risk to the participants.
As long as the public will buy tickets, watch on TV, buy sports apparel, cheer them on as heroes and call their names from the stands, anything goes.
The owners are indifferent to the well-being of their employees as long as they are profitable.
The idea that society owes a duty of protection to athletes who are budding millionaires, and choose their sport voluntarily, is quaint.
Although some may expect them to avoid activities that may result in their premature death, it is not our duty.
Capitalism is amoral, money talks, and ethics fall by the wayside.
When we see a wealthy 23-year -ld pextreme slorts payer being carried on an air stretcher after rupturing a disk in his back, we shrug and wait for the next match.
If the player is cured, you can bet they will be right back in the arena.
And if he is forced into retirement, then just wait for the movie and book deals.
Are certain sports too risky to engage in?
By what standards could this be even determined?
The players are making a living and could be open to putting their lives in danger, whether it turns out positively or negatively.
And the point of sports is to push limits and boundaries.
Sport cannot exist without taking risks.
As long as there is a demand for high-risk athletes, there will be someone willing to take the chances.
And that demand shows no sign of abating.
As long as the potential gains outweigh the dangers involved, extreme sports will continue to be practiced.
And we should remember that hardly anything is safe anyway.

For starters, audiobooks are useful when driving, strolling in the park, cooking, cleaning, or doing any other activity that requires you to be able to see what you 're doing rather than focusing on a a book.

Books offer no corresponding advantage, as the main activity that audiobooks might prevent, listening to music or other audio, is something that would also prevent the level of focus required to read a book.
That brings up another advantage of audiobooks, the fact that they not only free up our eyes, but don't require the same level of focus that reading does.

It's possible to attempt to read a book, and end up unable to follow what's going on and getting distracted and losing your place, while with an audiobook, you might well be able to make your way through the recording without getting distracted, and still retain what's going on in the story.
Audiobooks also better engage the imagination.

The sound of the words being read aloud, is immeasurably more evocative than their appearance on a page, and it's also the case that, when using sound rather than sight to engage our mental processes, we tend to engage them more fully, using both sides of our brain to process the resulting data, rather than just the one side that reading hard copy books activates.

There's also the fact that audiobook narrators are often good enough that they can add an extra dimension to the story, or just their reading voice in itself is worth listening to, which can not only elevate a decent story, but also enhance the experience of reading something that's otherwise uninteresting by itself.
Audiobooks are also accessible in areas where books may not be available.

Not everyone has a tablet, and many people attempting to read e-books on public transit or on trains experience difficulties like motion sickness, while doing so, either due to the glare on their screen or just the general inconvenience of reading while moving.
Also, audiobooks enable us to tune out distractions while listening to them on headphones in public settings like mass transit, whereas books lack the ability to do that.
In closing, audiobooks are in no regard worse than books, and in many ways, better.

If I were forced to choose one over the other, I'd have to say that, for me, as well as most people, the myriad extra benefits of listening to audiobooks would more than compensate for any loss that the lack of a printed page could entail.

The me that lived in the early 1900's was actually a professional and olympic athlete.
The common theme was that all of the people looking similar to me were athletic, the uncommon theme were the accents of speech, the personalities, and the life experiences.

As the numbers of humanity dwindle from alien bombardment, the creatures of magic, buoyed by the increase in free-floating Mana, begin to re-emerge.
The elves are the first ones to wake up after being in a magical slumber for the past few centuries.
Their charms and arrows prove to be surprisingly effective against alien armor, and beam weapons.
The next to stir are the dwarves, who have long been in hiding, and have been preparing for this day.
Dwarven siege engines and other primitive devices of destruction are even more effective against the aliens, and a dwarf trebuchet manages to, for the first time, bring down an alien ship.
After that, the goblins and other darker magical creatures begin to stir.

Finally, the dragons, the oldest of all magical creatures, awaken from their slumber.
Their fiery breath and claws are devastating against the aliens, and their armored scales are proof against their weapons.
The mere presence of the creatures often makes the most battle-hardened alien warriors flee in terror.
Meanwhile, the humans begin to discover their own latent magical abilities.
Now human mages can join in the battle, and their spells are the final ingredient that helps turn the tide of the war.
Within a few years, the aliens are defeated, and the survivors are able to begin rebuilding their civilization.

The war finally ends, with the last survivors of humanity forced to cling to a miserable, marginal existence on a world that is no longer truly theirs.

It basically gives you the chance to be more social in general.

You'd never know it if it wasn't for dating apps.

You really have nothing to lose and you may just find a new friend or the love of your life online.
It's worth a shot, especially in these lonely times of the pandemic.
